  , issueTitle = "r.http does not reuse connections"
  , issuePullRequest = Nothing
  , issueUrl =
      "https://api.github.com/repos/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/5255"
  , issueCreatedAt = 2016 (-01) (-05) 21 : 14 : 34 UTC
  , issueBody =
      Just
        "The very basic script:\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport rethinkdb as r\r\nc = r.connect()\r\nwhile True:\r\n    r.http(\"http://somewherelocal/\").run(c)\r\n```\r\n\r\nWill create and destroy an HTTP connection per iteration of the loop, instead of trying to reuse it.\r\n\r\nThis causes extra latency and system load, and under high load, can cause a system-wide failure to allocate new sockets, due to the system having too many sockets in the `TIME_WAIT` state ([which exists so that packets delayed/reordered by the network won't accidentally close connections made afterwards](http://superuser.com/questions/173535/what-are-close-wait-and-time-wait-states).) Trying to `connect(2)` somewhere while there are no ports available results in a fatal \"Cannot assign requested address\" error."
  , issueState = "open"
